Under the common trends assumption,
the TWFE coefficient beta, equal to 2.6339, estimates a weighted sum of 59 ATTs
> . 
27 ATTs receive a positive weight, and 32 receive a negative weight.
------------------------------------------------
Treat. var: st_stbafl1yr# ATTs      Σ weights  
------------------------------------------------
Positive weights        27          12.3038     
Negative weights        32          -11.3038    
------------------------------------------------
Total                   59          1.0000      
------------------------------------------------

Summary Measures:
TWFE coefficient (β_fe) =    2.6339
min σ(Δ) compatible with β_fe and Δ_TR = 0:    0.0800
min σ(Δ) compatible with treatment effect of opposite sign than β_fe in all (g,
> t) cells:    0.0873
Reference: Corollary 1, de Chaisemartin, C and D'Haultfoeuille, X (2020a)


The development of this package was funded by the European Union (ERC, REALLYCR
> EDIBLE,GA N°101043899).

. local tw_rc_fe1 = _rc

. 
. if `tw_rc_fe1' == 0 | `tw_rc_fe1' == 402 {
.     local tw_beta_fe1  = e(beta)
.     mat _M1 = e(M)
.     local tw_npos_fe1  = _M1[1,1]
.     local tw_nneg_fe1  = _M1[2,1]
.     local tw_pctN_fe1 : di %5.1f 100 * `tw_nneg_fe1' / (`tw_npos_fe1' + `tw_n
> neg_fe1')
.     di "  beta_TWFE  = " %10.6f `tw_beta_fe1'
  beta_TWFE  =   2.633853
.     di "  # pos wgts = " `tw_npos_fe1'
  # pos wgts = 27
.     di "  # neg wgts = " `tw_nneg_fe1'
  # neg wgts = 32
.     di "  % negative = " `tw_pctN_fe1' "%"
  % negative = 54.2%
. }

. else {
.     di "  feTR Col 1 FAILED with rc = `tw_rc_fe1'"
.     local tw_beta_fe1  = .
.     local tw_npos_fe1  = .
.     local tw_nneg_fe1  = .
.     local tw_pctN_fe1  = "---"
. }

. restore

